        a group a specific usage should be placed into, or null, if this rule doesn't apply to this kind of usages.

      • getParentGroupsFor

        public final java.util.List<UsageGroup> getParentGroupsFor(Usage usage,
                                                           UsageTarget [] targets)
        Description copied from interface: UsageGroupingRule
        Return list of nested parent groups for a usage. The specified usage will be placed into the last group from the list, that group will be placed under the next to last group, etc.

        If the rule returns at most one parent group extend SingleParentUsageGroupingRule and override getParentGroupFor instead.

        Specified by:
        getParentGroupsFor in interface UsageGroupingRule
